article.headline: Troy 86, Southeastern Louisiana 84
article.story: TROY, Ala. (AP) -- O'Darien Bassett scored 32 points and hit two key free throws in Troy's 86-84 victory over Southeastern Louisiana Saturday night. Bassett's free throws with 1:47 left gave the Trojans (4-2) a four-point cushion. Terry Bryant's 3-pointer cut Troy's lead to 86-84 with 40 seconds left after Sammy Sharp made 1-of-2 from the line. Jerome Odem then missed two free throws to give Southeastern Louisiana (4-1) another chance, but Patrick Sullivan missed a jump shot at the buzzer. Bassett led five double figure scorers for Troy. Odem scored 14 points, Sharp had 13, Richard Chaney 12 and Cedric Jackson 11. Bassett made 11-of-16 shots, including four 3-pointers, and made all six free throw attempts. Daryl Cohen led Southeastern Louisiana with 25 points, including seven 3-pointers. Quennell Green added 17 points and Kevyn Green 14.
